27/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) were killed on Wednesday (May 26th) in clashes with Turkish security forces in the eastern provinces of Tunceli and Bingol, security sources announced. Hundreds of soldiers were involved in the operation, one of the biggest of the past several months. According to local press reports, the four killed were suspected members of a group that attacked a patrol in Tunceli on April 30th, leaving five Turkish soldiers dead. (Hurriyet, Dogan, AP - 26/05/10)
